    <pubDate>2025</pubDate>
    <abstract>We present soil, total aboveground biomass, and necromass data for four mangrove transects. Two transects surveyed fringe ecotypes and two surveyed estuarine ecotypes. These areas were identified as land-use zones for the community of people who harvest mangrove cockle (Anadara tuberculosa) in the Gulf of Montijo, Veraguas. Data were collected between September and December 2019. The study provided information on the health of mangroves to the communities and the value of carbon stock services at the site.</abstract>
